The paper deals with the problem of assigning mobile users to basestations in order to maximize the sum-rate, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The problem involves making decisions based on incomplete information, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The algorithms proposed in the paper are based on online algorithms, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and networking (cs.NI). Finally, the paper uses techniques from optimization and machine learning, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG).
